                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/1691: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China (<persName type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-24T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 24, 1933—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>95. Your 268, March 21, 11 a.m. Department’s views remain unchanged and you are
                    therefore requested to follow the suggestions contained in its telegram 80,
                    March 10, 6 p.m. Note especially the last paragraph.</p>
                <pb facs="0769" n="667" xml:id="pg_667"/>
                <p>Department is informally approaching officials of the British and Italian
                    Embassies here, who have previously approached the Department in regard to this
                    subject, suggesting that appropriate instructions to your British and Italian
                    colleagues be expedited.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
